      • findUUID

        public java.util.UUID findUUID(java.lang.String key)
        Makes an attempt at retrieving a UUID from the JSON.

        Note: This works by casting the found key to a String, and then passing that in as the argument to the UUID.fromString(String) method. You should be positive that it was stored correctly when constructing the JSON.

        Parameters:
        key - The key that was used at creation
        Returns:
        A UUID from the provided String

      • find

        public <T> T find(java.lang.String key,
                  java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
        Grabs an object from the type provided as a class.

        Keep in mind that you may also attempt matching enumerators via this method. If the supplied parameter: clazz is of an enumeration type then we will attempt to grab from our JSON as a String, and then attempting to use a sort of Enum.valueOf(Class, String) to convert from this string to an object of that enum's type.

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of what we're requesting
        Parameters:
        key - The key that was stored at creation
        clazz - The type to cast to
        Returns:
        The found object. null if it does not exist
